WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.160
Good day!

00:06.160 --> 00:08.220
My name is Andrey Kulinich and I present the topic

00:08.220 --> 00:11.680
The main concepts of marketing, marketing concept of management.

00:11.680 --> 00:15.680
The concept of marketing was created in 1910.

00:15.680 --> 00:22.440
It is a conglomerate of two words mark-getting, that is, to take the market, to get the market.

00:22.440 --> 00:25.840
It is believed that the first marketing study was officially published

00:25.840 --> 00:33.640
in 1901, and it was a report of the Industrial Commission on Sales of Agricultural Products in the United States.

00:33.640 --> 00:39.080
In 1926, the American Association of Marketing and Advertising was created.

00:39.080 --> 00:43.960
On its basis, the American Society of Marketing was formed in the future.

00:43.960 --> 00:51.840
In the 1940s, the first systematization of marketing, marketing approach to enterprises appeared.

00:51.840 --> 00:57.760
In the 1950s, a term that has survived almost unchanged to this day,

00:57.760 --> 00:59.400
that is, marketing mix, appeared.

00:59.400 --> 01:06.040
In 1968, the first books on consumer behavior were published.

01:06.040 --> 01:11.480
If you look at the history of marketing in the Soviet Union and Russia,

01:11.480 --> 01:16.320
then for the first time it was officially discussed in the 1980s,

01:16.320 --> 01:22.840
when a course of marketing was conducted in the program of some universities.

01:22.840 --> 01:29.120
In 1995, the first standard of teaching marketing appeared in universities.

01:29.120 --> 01:31.720
Since then, it has undergone certain changes,

01:31.720 --> 01:38.720
but this profession still exists, and our universities train specialists in this field.

01:38.720 --> 01:41.920
There are a huge number of marketing departments.

01:41.920 --> 01:46.480
According to various estimates, there are from 1,500 to 2,500 of them.

01:46.480 --> 01:50.080
In fact, there are much more, but we just could not count them.

01:50.080 --> 01:58.960
Marketing is a science of the formation of differences that customers perceive and are ready to pay for them.

01:58.960 --> 02:00.400
This is one of the definitions.

02:00.400 --> 02:02.880
Marketing is a social management process,

02:02.880 --> 02:07.760
with the help of which individual persons and groups satisfy their needs

02:07.760 --> 02:12.200
and needs through the creation of goods and consumer values,

02:12.200 --> 02:14.680
and the exchange of them.

02:14.680 --> 02:16.680
This definition belongs to Philip Kotler.

02:16.680 --> 02:20.200
If we look at the official definition of marketing,

02:20.200 --> 02:26.800
then it is a process of planning and implementation of the concept of price formation,

02:26.800 --> 02:30.120
promotion and distribution of ideas, goods and services,

02:30.120 --> 02:36.000
for the exchange of goods and services, which satisfies the goals of individual people and enterprises.

02:36.240 --> 02:40.600
This definition belongs to the American Association of Marketing,

02:40.600 --> 02:44.520
which is considered the legislator of fashion in this industry.

02:44.520 --> 02:49.520
Marketing has changed, its definitions have changed.

02:49.520 --> 02:54.320
Initially, there was no need to promote goods,

02:54.320 --> 02:57.840
because demand on the market exceeded the offer.

02:58.160 --> 03:07.280
Remember the early 90s, when there were tickets for food, clothes, and other consumer goods.

03:07.280 --> 03:09.280
Why was there a need to promote products?

03:09.280 --> 03:14.160
All that our enterprises produced was actually available to its consumer.

03:14.160 --> 03:20.280
Nevertheless, at some point demand was equal to the offer,

03:20.600 --> 03:25.560
and the winners were those manufacturers and shops

03:25.560 --> 03:31.560
that were primarily focused on the quality of sales and intensification of sales.

03:31.560 --> 03:33.560
The situation is changing.

03:33.560 --> 03:36.040
At present, demand is less than the offer.

03:36.040 --> 03:41.760
Accordingly, there is some overproduction and competition for us, consumers.

03:41.760 --> 03:44.240
The market is changing.

03:44.240 --> 03:48.760
The market is changing, it is more and more focused on the consumer,

03:49.240 --> 03:52.240
and this is reflected in the increase of the service,

03:52.240 --> 03:57.240
in the creation of new goods that are more convenient for us and meet our needs.

03:57.240 --> 03:58.240
What's next?

03:58.240 --> 04:00.240
Next is social orientation.

04:00.240 --> 04:02.240
We'll talk about it in the next moment.

04:02.240 --> 04:09.240
Let's talk again about the key stages in which marketing has developed.

04:09.240 --> 04:15.240
First of all, the enterprises that were focused on the improvement of production have won.

04:15.720 --> 04:19.720
Namely, the reduction of the cost of production and quality management.

04:19.720 --> 04:25.720
Some enterprises are still at this stage and are not developing further.

04:25.720 --> 04:27.720
Why? Because there is no need for this.

04:27.720 --> 04:31.720
For example, if you are a supplier of oil and gas,

04:31.720 --> 04:34.720
where the consumer does not perceive the difference,

04:34.720 --> 04:39.720
where it is difficult to improve, and there is no need to improve the quality of these products,

04:39.720 --> 04:41.720
they meet the standards,

04:41.720 --> 04:47.720
but the one who has more production sites and saves on a large scale wins.

04:47.720 --> 04:50.720
And those who can do it cheaper.

04:50.720 --> 04:59.720
Nevertheless, after in other industries, such as food, clothes, cars, industrial equipment,

04:59.720 --> 05:05.720
enterprises learned to produce equally well and equally cheaply,

05:05.720 --> 05:09.720
new approaches and new concepts were necessary.

05:09.720 --> 05:12.720
The concept of marketing oriented to the improvement of goods has appeared.

05:12.720 --> 05:15.720
Good goods are not needed in advertising.

05:15.720 --> 05:18.720
This phrase refers to this stage.

05:18.720 --> 05:22.720
Why? Because if you release a good and high-quality product,

05:22.720 --> 05:27.720
which is in demand by your clients, which has no analogues,

05:27.720 --> 05:31.720
we pass the information about it from word of mouth.

05:31.720 --> 05:35.720
And it means that the product will promote itself on the market

05:35.720 --> 05:38.720
solely due to its consumer characteristics.

05:38.720 --> 05:45.720
But the characteristics that we, as consumers, need are limited.

05:45.720 --> 05:47.720
Their quantity is limited.

05:47.720 --> 05:53.720
And after some time, many goods begin to be absolutely similar to each other.

05:53.720 --> 05:55.720
We do not see an advantage in them.

05:55.720 --> 06:02.720
They have the same technical characteristics, other consumer qualities.

06:02.720 --> 06:04.720
Where to go next?

06:04.720 --> 06:08.720
Those who were oriented to intensify sales.

06:08.720 --> 06:15.720
At this stage, such a marketing tool as advertising was needed.

06:15.720 --> 06:18.720
The one who advertises more, sells more.

06:18.720 --> 06:22.720
We faced this in the late 90s and early 2000s.

06:22.720 --> 06:28.720
We were fed with advertising, but it was the main tool for promoting goods.

06:28.720 --> 06:31.720
We bought, among other things, goods that were known,

06:31.720 --> 06:34.720
which were actually imposed on us.

06:34.720 --> 06:36.720
Here we did not ask the opinion of the consumer,

06:36.720 --> 06:38.720
whether he liked the product, whether he liked the advertising.

06:38.720 --> 06:43.720
We were pushing the opinion of the product in the head,

06:43.720 --> 06:46.720
if I may say so, of the consumer,

06:46.720 --> 06:51.720
and educated cohorts of active aggressive sellers.

06:51.720 --> 06:54.720
The one who will run more, will sell more.

06:54.720 --> 06:55.720
It worked.

06:55.720 --> 07:00.720
But now, when we have something to choose from,

07:00.720 --> 07:07.720
when many manufacturers and suppliers have reached perfection in the field of advertising,

07:07.720 --> 07:09.720
when there is no way to increase advertising budgets,

07:09.720 --> 07:14.720
and their efficiency is decreasing every day,

07:14.720 --> 07:18.720
new ideas and approaches are needed.

07:18.720 --> 07:22.720
We avoid pressure and choose those goods,

07:22.720 --> 07:25.720
which are more in line with our needs.

07:25.720 --> 07:28.720
It means that manufacturers, suppliers and sellers

07:28.720 --> 07:32.720
should take into account the interests of our consumers,

07:32.720 --> 07:38.720
and make goods and services that are in line with our needs.

07:38.720 --> 07:44.720
It is impossible to create goods and services that are good for everyone at the same time.

07:44.720 --> 07:47.720
This is marketing of the marketing niche segments.

07:47.720 --> 07:49.720
This is targeted marketing.

07:49.720 --> 07:52.720
It is the orientation of the consumer.

07:52.720 --> 07:55.720
It is important to understand what the consumer wants,

07:55.720 --> 07:58.720
what he wants, what he is ready to pay for,

07:58.720 --> 08:00.720
and offer him this.

08:00.720 --> 08:03.720
High service, orientation of the consumer,

08:03.720 --> 08:04.720
things are not cheap.

08:04.720 --> 08:10.720
The concept of raising prices or making a profit is related to this.

08:10.720 --> 08:12.720
But our prosperity is growing.

08:12.720 --> 08:16.720
We are ready to pay for the goods and products that are convenient for us.

08:16.720 --> 08:19.720
What is next? The world does not stop.

08:19.720 --> 08:21.720
Some Western countries and developed countries

08:21.720 --> 08:24.720
are already living on the social and ethical concept of marketing.

08:24.720 --> 08:32.720
When we choose goods that are more in line with our social status,

08:32.720 --> 08:42.720
we wear suits, we buy cars that are in line with our position in society.

08:42.720 --> 08:46.720
Ethical marketing is another side of the same coin.

08:46.720 --> 08:50.720
When there are goods that are of the same quality,

08:50.720 --> 08:55.720
not expensive, with the same characteristics,

08:55.720 --> 09:00.720
known and convenient for us as consumers,

09:00.720 --> 09:04.720
we look for additional reasons to choose one or another product.

09:04.720 --> 09:08.720
Accordingly, at a high level of prosperity,

09:08.720 --> 09:15.720
we choose goods that are more environmentally friendly.

09:15.720 --> 09:20.720
That is, when they are made, the least environmental damage was done.

09:20.720 --> 09:24.720
We choose goods of those manufacturers

09:24.720 --> 09:29.720
that comply with social and ethical norms in relation to their employees.

09:29.720 --> 09:32.720
We do not use, for example, child labor,

09:32.720 --> 09:37.720
or the proportion of women and men in the management staff.

09:37.720 --> 09:40.720
The proportion is approximately equal.

09:40.720 --> 09:43.720
It is important to understand that the type of competition

09:43.720 --> 09:46.720
in which you live changes according to the definition of marketing.

09:46.720 --> 09:49.720
Pure competition is quite rare.

09:49.720 --> 09:52.720
Pure competition is associated with stock markets,

09:52.720 --> 09:56.720
when there are many buyers and sellers,

09:56.720 --> 09:59.720
and buyers do not see significant differences

09:59.720 --> 10:01.720
except for the price in these goods.

10:01.720 --> 10:03.720
We have already talked about such goods.

10:03.720 --> 10:06.720
Oil, gas, sugar, flour in wholesale supplies

10:06.720 --> 10:09.720
must correspond to a certain cost.

10:09.720 --> 10:10.720
No more, no less.

10:10.720 --> 10:14.720
And why should I pay more for the same goods as a buyer?

10:14.720 --> 10:15.720
No, I will not.

10:15.720 --> 10:17.720
This is pure competition.

10:17.720 --> 10:21.720
That is, there is a struggle exclusively at the expense of the price.

10:21.720 --> 10:24.720
Monopolistic competition is not a monopoly.

10:24.720 --> 10:26.720
I ask you not to confuse.

10:26.720 --> 10:32.720
Monopolistic competition implies the presence of a large number of buyers

10:32.720 --> 10:34.720
and a large number of sellers.

10:34.720 --> 10:38.720
But buyers see significant differences in goods.

10:38.720 --> 10:42.720
They perceive them differently and evaluate them differently.

10:42.720 --> 10:45.720
For example, cars.

10:45.720 --> 10:50.720
There are quite a lot of manufacturers and quite a lot of buyers.

10:50.720 --> 10:54.720
But we understand or can explain to ourselves

10:54.720 --> 10:58.720
why BMW cars are more expensive than AvtoVAZ cars.

10:58.720 --> 11:02.720
We see these differences and are ready to pay various money.

11:02.720 --> 11:08.720
In this case, AvtoVAZ and Mercedes cars do not directly compete with each other.

11:08.720 --> 11:13.720
They have different consumers, both in terms of needs and in terms of profitability.

11:13.720 --> 11:19.720
If we talk about competition, then most likely BMW cars

11:19.720 --> 11:23.720
compete primarily with Mercedes, Audi, but not with a low price segment.

11:23.720 --> 11:29.720
That is, monopolistic competition implies a large number of buyers and sellers,

11:29.720 --> 11:34.720
but buyers see significant differences in goods.

11:34.720 --> 11:51.720
Oligopolistic competition implies the presence of 2-3 largest players in the market.

11:51.720 --> 11:57.720
For example, 3 large companies own 50-60% of the market.

11:57.720 --> 12:01.720
This means that there is no competition.

12:01.720 --> 12:05.720
They are about the same in strength and financial resources.

12:05.720 --> 12:13.720
And the main or smaller players are more likely to be guided by their behavior.

12:13.720 --> 12:19.720
It is these players who dictate the main conditions of competition,

12:19.720 --> 12:23.720
the main rules, the values, channels of promotion,

12:23.720 --> 12:29.720
and in fact have the opportunity to squeeze out small competitors.

12:29.720 --> 12:33.720
Oligopolistic competition implies that there is no competition.

12:33.720 --> 12:39.720
Moreover, sudden changes from the side of the largest players

12:39.720 --> 12:48.720
can lead to a price war and the winner will not be in equal conditions and resources.

12:48.720 --> 12:53.720
They understand this perfectly and try to coordinate their actions in one way or another,

12:53.720 --> 12:55.720
to develop as smoothly as possible.

12:55.720 --> 13:03.720
As a rule, the whole world comes to the mature stages of the market life cycle in the case of oligopolistic competition.

13:03.720 --> 13:09.720
That is, when the market is already stable or is declining.

13:09.720 --> 13:12.720
In Russia, unfortunately, the situation is a little different.

13:12.720 --> 13:14.720
This is due to non-standard development.

13:14.720 --> 13:17.720
When it was possible to acquire a whole industry,

13:17.720 --> 13:24.720
and they were concentrated in the hands of a small number of owners, a small number of enterprises.

13:24.720 --> 13:29.720
Therefore, the oligopolistic stage in the whole world, as a rule,

13:29.720 --> 13:34.720
corresponds to the orientation of the consumer or social and ethical marketing.

13:34.720 --> 13:42.720
In Russia, oligopolistic competition can exist in the situation of the orientation to production or to the improvement of the product.

13:42.720 --> 13:47.720
And you don't have to expect a significant change in the offer from their side.

13:47.720 --> 13:49.720
A pure monopoly.

13:49.720 --> 13:51.720
One seller.

13:51.720 --> 13:53.720
No one to choose from.

13:53.720 --> 13:55.720
You can give such examples yourself.

13:55.720 --> 13:59.720
Gazprom, Rao ES, and so on.

14:01.720 --> 14:09.720
It is important to understand that marketing changes the perception and the pursuit of the owner.

14:09.720 --> 14:14.720
Initially, the concept was oriented to the product out.

14:14.720 --> 14:16.720
That is, pushing the product to the market.

14:16.720 --> 14:19.720
We produce, we impose it.

14:19.720 --> 14:28.720
But at some point, there were a lot of products that we were trying to impose.

14:28.720 --> 14:30.720
The efficiency was not so high.

14:30.720 --> 14:32.720
And the market has changed.

14:32.720 --> 14:34.720
The concept of product in has appeared.

14:34.720 --> 14:37.720
We attract the market.

14:37.720 --> 14:47.720
We create goods that interest the customers, so that they come to us and leave their money.

14:47.720 --> 14:51.720
There was an exchange of goods, money, goods.

14:51.720 --> 14:56.720
But now we see vivid examples of invest-in.

14:56.720 --> 15:01.720
When companies earn not by selling goods or services,

15:01.720 --> 15:06.720
but they earn by placing their shares or bonds on the market.

15:06.720 --> 15:12.720
For example, the sale of a small package of shares to Wimbledon

15:12.720 --> 15:18.720
brought much more income to the owners than the company's profit over 10 years.

15:18.720 --> 15:27.720
That is, now you can create an attractive company for investors,

15:27.720 --> 15:32.720
but not earn on consumers,

15:32.720 --> 15:40.720
but earn by selling or trading shares on the market or selling to a strategic investor.

15:40.720 --> 15:47.720
Accordingly, the object of marketing is not a consumer, but a potential investor.

15:47.720 --> 15:55.720
It is important to understand that the development of marketing affects the development of marketing in the company of a large circle of interested parties.

15:56.720 --> 16:04.720
It is important to understand that the main marketers in the company are the owners and the CEO.

16:04.720 --> 16:12.720
They determine how the company perceives the client, what it is ready to do for him and for what money.

16:12.720 --> 16:15.720
Top managers can be considered as interested parties,

16:15.720 --> 16:23.720
who, through their vision, pass the orders of the managers and give them down.

16:23.720 --> 16:25.720
They manage the company's activities.

16:25.720 --> 16:33.720
Also, hired managers, hired employees, suppliers, buyers, partners, local authorities,

16:33.720 --> 16:39.720
which either limit or promote competition, also influence the marketing in the company.

16:39.720 --> 16:46.720
So, we have considered a number of conditions in which marketing exists.

16:47.720 --> 17:01.720
Please note that when competition, monopoly, oligopoly, pure monopoly, and the concept of marketing intersect,

17:01.720 --> 17:04.720
different conditions of its existence arise.

17:04.720 --> 17:13.720
And the definition of marketing for each cell, for each intersection will be different.

17:13.720 --> 17:21.720
And if we take into account that the group of interested parties, which we have listed above, also influences the definition of marketing,

17:21.720 --> 17:26.720
then in these conditions, the definition of marketing can be an infinite number.

17:26.720 --> 17:28.720
Here are some of them.

17:28.720 --> 17:33.720
Marketing is advertising, promoting sales and imposing goods on the buyer.

17:33.720 --> 17:36.720
A complex of aggressive sales tools.

17:36.720 --> 17:37.720
Isn't it true?

17:37.720 --> 17:42.720
It is clearly visible at what stage of development the company is in terms of marketing.

17:42.720 --> 17:47.720
Marketing is a complex of tools for market analysis, such as methods of forecasting sales volumes,

17:47.720 --> 17:55.720
imitation models, various market researches, which are used for a deeper scientific approach to analysis of demand and demand.

17:55.720 --> 17:57.720
An interesting definition.

17:57.720 --> 18:02.720
What stage of marketing does it correspond to in your opinion?

18:02.720 --> 18:07.720
There can be many definitions, some of them are funny.

18:08.720 --> 18:12.720
Marketing is all and all is marketing.

18:12.720 --> 18:19.720
Marketing is all that a consumer thinks about the company, said Peter Drucker.

18:19.720 --> 18:27.720
Marketing is all that managers do not want to do on sales, do not have time or cannot, as Igor Ryman said.

18:27.720 --> 18:28.720
Think about it.

18:28.720 --> 18:31.720
And what is the definition of marketing of your company?

18:31.720 --> 18:34.720
Give a short definition.

18:34.720 --> 18:36.720
Marketing is...

18:38.720 --> 18:42.720
Whatever you call a boat, it will swim.

18:42.720 --> 18:44.720
This is what marketing is.

18:46.720 --> 18:49.720
Let's get back to what influences the marketing of a company.

18:49.720 --> 18:53.720
Pay attention to the slide with the triad of Philip Kotler.

18:53.720 --> 18:59.720
Philip Kotler presented the marketing of a company as a triangle, at the top of which is the leader.

18:59.720 --> 19:06.720
I repeat once again that the main marketer in a company, the one who sets the tone, is the leader.

19:06.720 --> 19:13.720
Accordingly, in terms of angles, it is internal marketing, that is, the side between the leader and the staff.

19:13.720 --> 19:21.720
This is how the leader conveys his thoughts, the vision of the market, the understanding of the buyer, the understanding of the market strategy of the company.

19:21.720 --> 19:26.720
The second side is the connection between the leader and the client.

19:26.720 --> 19:30.720
This is the marketing that the company conducts on the market.

19:30.720 --> 19:39.720
If the leader does not understand who his clients are, what they want, then the marketing will be ineffective.

19:39.720 --> 19:49.720
It is important to understand that the staff that implements the strategy or vision of the leader is also an important component of the marketing.

19:49.720 --> 19:59.720
The way the staff understands the tasks and goals that are set by the leader, they implement through the relationship with the client.

19:59.720 --> 20:01.720
This is how they treat the client.

20:01.720 --> 20:07.720
In my opinion, the best representation of marketing in a company belongs to Jacques-Jean Lambin.

20:07.720 --> 20:09.720
Pay attention to the slide.

20:09.720 --> 20:14.720
Jacques-Jean Lambin says that marketing is three main aspects.

20:15.720 --> 20:23.720
First of all, it is the business philosophy, how you conduct it, what are the values of the company, what are the values for the market you create.

20:23.720 --> 20:29.720
This is exactly what the leader transmits inside the company.

20:29.720 --> 20:37.720
This is a set of marketing tools, methods, approaches, techniques, algorithms, tables.

20:37.720 --> 20:42.720
This is what is most understandable in marketing, but it does not work without philosophy.

20:42.720 --> 20:46.720
They are either a continuation or a tool.

20:46.720 --> 20:52.720
The third important thing for effective marketing is marketing as a function of management in the company.

20:52.720 --> 21:05.720
Marketing should have the power to plan, organize, motivate, execute and control the tasks set.

21:06.720 --> 21:11.720
Marketing should be a tool, it should be a force.

21:11.720 --> 21:13.720
Marketing is divided into two levels.

21:13.720 --> 21:17.720
There are two levels of marketing.

21:17.720 --> 21:21.720
Strategic marketing and tactical marketing.

21:21.720 --> 21:30.720
Strategic marketing is usually related to the analysis of the needs of the market, segmentation of the market,

21:30.720 --> 21:42.720
that is, dividing it into parts, how the company's proposals are perceived in relation to the company's competitiveness,

21:42.720 --> 21:47.720
highlighting the most promising segments in which the company will operate in the future.

21:47.720 --> 21:54.720
This is the analysis of competition and participation in the development of the company's strategy.

21:55.720 --> 22:05.720
Tactical marketing or operational marketing is a choice as a goal of the market segments determined at the stage of strategic marketing.

22:05.720 --> 22:19.720
The definition of a marketing mix is the definition of the marketing budget,

22:19.720 --> 22:28.720
the promotion of the product to the market and the execution and control of the goals set at the stage of strategic planning.

22:28.720 --> 22:30.720
So, marketing.

22:30.720 --> 22:38.720
If we talk about the functions of marketing, then the main functions are the formation of a production strategy,

22:38.720 --> 22:42.720
support of the sales department in promoting the product,

22:42.720 --> 22:52.720
supply of information about the situation in the market to the company's managers to make decisions about the company's actions,

22:52.720 --> 22:59.720
coordination of the actions of the company's main departments in order to meet the needs of the clients.

22:59.720 --> 23:03.720
Why has marketing become relevant now?

23:04.720 --> 23:06.720
First of all, it is about increasing the competition.

23:06.720 --> 23:15.720
We have already discussed that at some point the balance in the market was broken and the demand was lower than the supply.

23:15.720 --> 23:23.720
This means that it is necessary to better convey and better meet the needs of the client in what you do.

23:23.720 --> 23:26.720
The needs of the client are changing.

23:27.720 --> 23:29.720
Our welfare is growing.

23:29.720 --> 23:37.720
We have new desires, new consumer experience, and the company needs to follow its consumers.

23:37.720 --> 23:39.720
Our preferences are changing.

23:39.720 --> 23:44.720
We can afford to buy something better.

23:44.720 --> 23:49.720
It is important to understand that today we are competing with you on the global market.

23:49.720 --> 23:53.720
Already now, despite the fact that we are in Russia.

