30:33.720 --> 30:42.720
That is, we, buying goods for our own consumption, stimulate the development of all other industries.

30:45.720 --> 30:49.720
It is important to understand what is the market capacity in marketing.

30:49.720 --> 30:52.720
That is, the market capacity on which we work.

30:52.720 --> 30:56.720
And here are two types of capacity.

30:56.720 --> 31:04.720
The real market capacity is the actual sales volume of the product or service.

31:04.720 --> 31:09.720
That is, the volume of the paymentable demand under certain conditions.

31:09.720 --> 31:21.720
That is, if we say that last year consumers purchased a couple of billion rubles of tourist services in the money equivalent,

31:21.720 --> 31:25.720
that is, this is the real market capacity.

31:25.720 --> 31:30.720
But at the same time, the second parameter is the potential market capacity.

31:30.720 --> 31:34.720
That is, the maximum sales volume in a market situation,

31:34.720 --> 31:41.720
when all potential consumers purchase goods based on the maximum possible level of consumption.

31:41.720 --> 31:52.720
That is, everyone has the opportunity and the need for these goods, and there is an opportunity to pay for the purchase of these services.

31:52.720 --> 31:58.720
The difference between the real market capacity and the potential market capacity is called the market potential.

31:58.720 --> 32:04.720
The market potential will be important for us, including for determining the life stage of the market,

32:04.720 --> 32:08.720
either goods or services, in subsequent analyzes.

32:08.720 --> 32:11.720
Several types of marketing are highlighted.

32:11.720 --> 32:13.720
First of all, this is mass marketing.

32:13.720 --> 32:21.720
When you offer the same type, the same characteristics for all consumers, for the same price, goods.

32:21.720 --> 32:24.720
That is, you do not select target groups.

32:24.720 --> 32:32.720
This type of marketing is possible under low competition,

32:32.720 --> 32:40.720
